Gives me strength to carry on.

33
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:03,400
So please keep fighting.

34
00:03:03,840 --> 00:03:04,840
The rain today.

35
00:03:05,480 --> 00:03:06,960
Means sunshine tomorrow.

36
00:03:10,720 --> 00:03:12,640
My supporters will always be here.

37
00:03:16,463 --> 00:03:18,663
My supporters will always be here.

38
00:03:27,120 --> 00:03:29,200
My supporters will always be here.

39
00:03:40,640 --> 00:03:41,640
Alright.

40
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:43,600
No more waiting to die.

41
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:47,320
You were quitting the
industry five minutes ago.

42
00:03:48,240 --> 00:03:49,560
Fang Runzhi's Visionary Talent.

43
00:03:50,440 --> 00:03:52,360
Has been wanting to sign me, right.

44
00:03:53,520 --> 00:03:54,560
Get them on the line.

45
00:03:54,840 --> 00:03:55,640
Yes.

46
00:03:55,800 --> 00:03:56,800
Also.

47
00:03:58,040 --> 00:03:59,560
Draft a reply to this fan.

48
00:04:00,600 --> 00:04:03,040
Tell them to focus on recovery.

49
00:04:04,880 --> 00:04:05,920
Watch me.

50
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:09,320
Shine brighter than ever.

51
00:04:10,200 --> 00:04:11,200
Got it.

52
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:14,120
Include a signed photo.

53
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:16,000
Boss.

54
00:04:16,080 --> 00:04:19,120
This is the first time you've
cared this much about a fan.

55
00:04:31,800 --> 00:04:35,800
(Episode 3)

56
00:04:40,680 --> 00:04:42,080
It can't be him, right.

57
00:04:49,400 --> 00:04:50,560
What's with the stubbornness.

58
00:04:50,840 --> 00:04:52,160
Who's the real child here.

59
00:04:57,600 --> 00:04:59,040
What a corny analogy.

60
00:05:02,800 --> 00:05:03,600
That analogy is just.

61
00:05:03,600 --> 00:05:04,400
Brother Jia.

62
00:05:04,440 --> 00:05:05,240
Are you at the hotel.

63
00:05:05,280 --> 00:05:06,080
Yes.

64
00:05:06,200 --> 00:05:07,000
That analogy is too...

65
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:08,000
Uh.

66
00:05:08,816 --> 00:05:11,416
Bring a clean towel to VIP Suite 1.

67
00:05:11,840 --> 00:05:12,640
Right away.

68
00:05:12,800 --> 00:05:14,080
No one's in the room.

69
00:05:16,320 --> 00:05:19,320
Deliver a clean towel to VIP Suite 1.

70
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:21,120
Understood, Brother Jia.

71
00:05:21,200 --> 00:05:22,440
No one told you to look for me.

72
00:05:22,720 --> 00:05:23,960
No one told you to look for me.

73
00:05:29,680 --> 00:05:30,560
Brother Jia, open up.

74
00:05:30,600 --> 00:05:31,640
Keep knocking.

75
00:05:36,200 --> 00:05:38,000
Brother Jia, let me in.

76
00:05:39,520 --> 00:05:41,520
Why would I ask you for a towel.

77
00:05:42,200 --> 00:05:42,880
Huh.

78
00:05:42,881 --> 00:05:44,760
Use your damn head.

79
00:05:48,440 --> 00:05:49,560
Leave the takeout outside.

80
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:50,640
Thanks.

81
00:05:51,640 --> 00:05:52,720
Just say it's you.

82
00:05:53,120 --> 00:05:54,200
It's Teacher Su.

83
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:56,440
It's Teacher Su.

84
00:06:04,800 --> 00:06:05,400
Ah.

85
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:06,080
It's you.

86
00:06:06,400 --> 00:06:07,600
Teacher Pei's showering.

87
00:06:07,840 --> 00:06:08,440
Hmm.

88
00:06:08,480 --> 00:06:09,680
Bringing him a towel.

89
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:15,680
*forced cough*

90
00:06:33,320 --> 00:06:35,319
You should rest now

91
00:06:35,320 --> 00:06:36,320
I won't disturb you.

92
00:06:38,520 --> 00:06:39,520
Oh, Brother Jia.

93
00:06:39,920 --> 00:06:43,120
The director wants you and
Teacher Su in his suite by 5.

94
00:06:43,200 --> 00:06:44,720
For tomorrow's important scene.

95
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:46,000
Noted.

96
00:06:46,920 --> 00:06:48,920
CEO Fang is visiting the set today.

97
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:50,200
He requested to have dinner with you

98
00:06:50,320 --> 00:06:51,520
I already declined.

99
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:53,440
But he insists it's mandatory.

100
00:06:54,800 --> 00:06:55,800
Tell him I'm asleep.

101
00:06:56,320 --> 00:06:57,320
Will do

102
00:06:57,640 --> 00:06:59,040
I'll take my leave now.

103
00:07:00,200 --> 00:07:01,200
Wait a moment.

104
00:07:02,320 --> 00:07:03,400
It's almost 5 o'clock

105
00:07:03,440 --> 00:07:04,640
I'll go first.

106
00:07:08,080 --> 00:07:09,600
What's wrong with Teacher Su.

107
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:12,800
Brat.

108
00:07:14,240 --> 00:07:15,440
Why did Fang Runzhi come.

109
00:07:16,520 --> 00:07:17,120
Not sure.

110
00:07:17,200 --> 00:07:18,480
He just showed up suddenly.

111
00:07:18,720 --> 00:07:20,520
Seems like something urgent.

112
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:25,800
The most urgent thing now is to
terminate my contract immediately.

113
00:07:26,600 --> 00:07:27,800
Oh, Mr. Fang.

114
00:07:28,400 --> 00:07:30,200
I'm rehearsing with two actors.

115
00:07:31,040 --> 00:07:32,160
Let's skip the meal.

116
00:07:32,200 --> 00:07:33,240
We'll have chances later.

117
00:07:33,840 --> 00:07:34,320
Ah.

118
00:07:34,720 --> 00:07:36,560
It's mainly because your
visit was unexpected.

119
00:07:37,080 --> 00:07:38,080
Oh, right

120
00:07:38,240 --> 00:07:40,880
I'll contact you after rehearsal, okay.

121
00:07:40,920 --> 00:07:41,920
Hey hey hey.

122
00:07:43,600 --> 00:07:44,600
Investor.

123
00:07:45,480 --> 00:07:47,400
What do you think?
Your brother didn't tell you.

124
00:07:47,640 --> 00:07:49,560
If Mr. Fang hadn't invested.

125
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:50,720
Our show would be cancelled.

126
00:07:51,480 --> 00:07:52,000
Huh.

127
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:53,000
Oh, by the way.

128
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:54,160
For the dinner later.

129
00:07:54,200 --> 00:07:54,720
You're coming too.

130
00:07:55,040 --> 00:07:56,040
Oh.

131
00:07:56,600 --> 00:07:57,440
Su Yi is still young.

132
00:07:57,440 --> 00:07:58,240
Why make him go.

133
00:07:58,241 --> 00:07:59,480
He should focus on acting.

134
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:02,240
Fang Runzhi specifically requested him.

135
00:08:03,176 --> 00:08:04,255
Why does he want him there.

136
00:08:04,280 --> 00:08:05,080
Ask him yourself.

137
00:08:05,080 --> 00:08:06,080
Never mind.

138
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:07,400
Let's focus on rehearsal.

139
00:08:08,520 --> 00:08:09,520
Hey.

140
00:08:09,680 --> 00:08:10,960
Teacher Pei, perfect timing.

141
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:12,120
Here's the thing.

142
00:08:12,121 --> 00:08:13,639
Su Bai and I.

143
00:08:13,640 --> 00:08:15,360
Designed a game for you two.

144
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:17,240
To prepare for tomorrow's intimate scene.

145
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:18,800
Director

146
00:08:18,801 --> 00:08:20,200
I don't think that's necessary.

147
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:21,680
Wasn't today's rehearsal good enough?

148
00:08:22,720 --> 00:08:23,760
Not enough.

149
00:08:23,800 --> 00:08:25,520
Not enough, come on.

150
00:08:26,200 --> 00:08:26,720
Sit.

151
00:08:26,800 --> 00:08:27,800
Haha.

152
00:08:29,196 --> 00:08:30,320
Here's the plan.

153
00:08:30,400 --> 00:08:32,039
Since Mr. Fang is coming tomorrow.

154
00:08:32,040 --> 00:08:32,440
Right.

155
00:08:32,480 --> 00:08:33,920
We can't disappoint him.

156
00:08:34,120 --> 00:08:34,800
Come, Su Bai.

157
00:08:34,840 --> 00:08:36,040
Explain the game rules.

158
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:38,040
This game.

159
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:39,560
Has 36 questions total

160
00:08:39,720 --> 00:08:40,960
I selected 8-10.

161
00:08:42,120 --> 00:08:42,520
Here.

162
00:08:42,520 --> 00:08:43,520
Take a look.

163
00:08:47,320 --> 00:08:48,640
What kind of game is this?

164
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:51,799
This helps you two quickly build.

165
00:08:51,800 --> 00:08:53,320
An emotional connection.

166
00:08:53,600 --> 00:08:55,680
From a famous American psychologist, named...

167
00:08:55,720 --> 00:08:56,720
Arthur Aron.

168
00:08:57,400 --> 00:08:58,000
Right.

169
00:08:58,001 --> 00:09:00,000
Oh, you know about this.

170
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:02,239
I came across it before.

171
00:09:02,240 --> 00:09:03,880
But don't really understand it.

172
00:09:05,120 --> 00:09:06,120
Just review it.

173
00:09:06,121 --> 00:09:08,120
These are simplified versions.

174
00:09:08,240 --> 00:09:09,840
Start when you're ready.

175
00:09:10,320 --> 00:09:11,960
The director and I will smoke downstairs.

176
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:13,720
Starting now.

177
00:09:13,840 --> 00:09:14,880
What else would you do.

178
00:09:16,880 --> 00:09:17,880
Take care.

179
00:09:19,040 --> 00:09:20,040
Bye bro.

180
00:09:26,120 --> 00:09:26,600
Hey.

181
00:09:26,920 --> 00:09:27,999
What.

182
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:29,160
You actually want to do this.

183
00:09:30,520 --> 00:09:32,720
If it helps with acting

184
00:09:32,840 --> 00:09:33,840
I'll do it.

185
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:35,840
I don't have time for this.

186
00:09:36,120 --> 00:09:38,120
Then why didn't you say that earlier.

187
00:09:39,040 --> 00:09:40,040
Bullying the weak.

188
00:09:43,480 --> 00:09:44,679
Fine.

189
00:09:44,680 --> 00:09:45,680
Come on.

190
00:09:47,920 --> 00:09:48,920
First question.

191
00:09:49,031 --> 00:09:50,748
Do you want to be famous? How
would you achieve that?

192
00:09:51,170 --> 00:09:53,155
I do, from acting.

193
00:09:53,520 --> 00:09:55,960
Because I realized I really enjoy acting.

194
00:09:56,440 --> 00:09:57,320
Though for you.

195
00:09:57,400 --> 00:09:59,000
It's just part of your routine.

196
00:09:59,040 --> 00:09:59,960
But for me.

197
00:09:59,984 --> 00:10:01,984
Do you have a secret
premonition about the future?

198
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:03,080
I wasn't finished.

199
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:05,800
"You do, from acting."

200
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:07,000
Didn't we finish talking.

201
00:10:07,680 --> 00:10:09,199
Alright, then it's my turn to ask.

202
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:11,700
What do you think a perfect day is like?

203
00:10:11,720 --> 00:10:12,720
Sleep.

204
00:10:13,280 --> 00:10:15,280
Do you have a secret
premonition about the future?

205
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:17,000
Actually yes.

206
00:10:19,200 --> 00:10:21,040
Maybe death.

207
00:10:21,720 --> 00:10:23,040
That's stating the obvious.

208
00:10:23,080 --> 00:10:24,296
Is that supposed to be a secret.

209
00:10:24,320 --> 00:10:25,320
Of course.

210
00:10:26,300 --> 00:10:29,300
What do you think of your
relationship with your mother?

211
00:10:29,400 --> 00:10:30,400
That's private.

212
00:10:33,100 --> 00:10:34,599
Are you close with your family?

213
00:10:34,600 --> 00:10:35,400
That's private.

214
00:10:35,559 --> 00:10:38,159
What role do love and
emotions play in your life?

215
00:10:38,280 --> 00:10:39,280
That's private.

216
00:10:40,600 --> 00:10:42,800
Can you share an embarrassing moment?

217
00:10:42,880 --> 00:10:43,880
Now.

218
00:10:47,400 --> 00:10:48,640
How many questions?

219
00:10:52,320 --> 00:10:53,320
Seven.

220
00:10:53,400 --> 00:10:54,600
Then this is the last one.

221
00:10:54,700 --> 00:10:58,300
If you could invite anyone,
who would you invite to dinner with you?

222
00:10:58,320 --> 00:10:59,120
Wrap.

223
00:10:59,120 --> 00:11:00,120
You.

224
00:11:22,320 --> 00:11:23,760
Have we really never met before?

225
00:11:35,400 --> 00:11:36,400
No.

226
00:11:54,040 --> 00:11:55,240
Ah.

227
00:12:01,200 --> 00:12:02,400
Why send Su Yi.

228
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:05,200
Just a dinner.

229
00:12:05,480 --> 00:12:07,240
You know what kind of
person Fang Runzhi is.

230
00:12:08,640 --> 00:12:09,640
The investor.

231
00:12:09,800 --> 00:12:10,800
Don't play dumb.

232
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:13,280
It's just a dinner.

233
00:12:13,720 --> 00:12:14,960
Tell Su Yi to watch his words.

234
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:16,800
We'll all be there to keep an eye out

235
00:12:18,400 --> 00:12:19,799
But.

236
00:12:19,800 --> 00:12:21,040
Something feels off.

237
00:12:22,800 --> 00:12:24,400
He's in the film industry.

238
00:12:24,480 --> 00:12:25,880
Rumors are common

239
00:12:26,200 --> 00:12:27,200
I've met him a few times.

240
00:12:27,600 --> 00:12:28,600
He's decent.

241
00:12:33,080 --> 00:12:35,160
Su Yi came to me alone this time.

242
00:12:35,400 --> 00:12:36,480
Without telling his family.

243
00:12:37,200 --> 00:12:38,360
I must take good care of him.

244
00:12:40,400 --> 00:12:41,440
Fang Runzhi is calling.

245
00:12:41,480 --> 00:12:42,480
Let's go.

246
00:12:58,600 --> 00:12:59,800
Mr. Fang.

247
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:01,720
Director Yi, thanks for your hard work.

248
00:13:01,800 --> 00:13:02,720
Finally here.

249
00:13:02,721 --> 00:13:04,200
Thanks for making time.

250
00:13:04,240 --> 00:13:05,360
To join us for dinner.

251
00:13:05,400 --> 00:13:07,400
Everyone knows you're busy, Mr. Fang.

252
00:13:07,440 --> 00:13:08,839
Honored you'd dine with our small crew.

253
00:13:08,840 --> 00:13:09,840
Truly

254
00:13:09,880 --> 00:13:12,120
I have a big scene tomorrow.

255
00:13:12,400 --> 00:13:13,280
Wrapped early today.

256
00:13:13,320 --> 00:13:14,320
No shop talk.

257
00:13:15,680 --> 00:13:16,880
And these are...

258
00:13:16,920 --> 00:13:19,640
Our screenwriter Su Bai.

259
00:13:19,680 --> 00:13:21,360
And this is Su Yi.

260
00:13:21,400 --> 00:13:22,400
An up-and-coming actor.

261
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:26,080
Pei Jia needs no introduction.

262
00:13:26,720 --> 00:13:27,360
Well.

263
00:13:27,400 --> 00:13:28,720
How's Pei Jia been lately.

264
00:13:29,080 --> 00:13:30,200
Not throwing diva tantrums

265
00:13:30,240 --> 00:13:31,560
I've warned him many times.

266
00:13:31,920 --> 00:13:32,560
No.

267
00:13:32,600 --> 00:13:34,199
Pei Jia gets along great with us.

268
00:13:34,200 --> 00:13:35,200
Right.

269
00:13:35,480 --> 00:13:38,120
He's often giving pointers to the other actors.

270
00:13:38,320 --> 00:13:39,919
Stealing my director's job.

271
00:13:39,920 --> 00:13:40,400
So.

272
00:13:40,440 --> 00:13:42,040
We're left dining with you.

273
00:13:42,200 --> 00:13:43,600
Enough formalities.

274
00:13:43,640 --> 00:13:44,560
Let's eat.

275
00:13:44,600 --> 00:13:46,000
Please, have a seat.

276
00:13:48,880 --> 00:13:49,720
Su Yi.

277
00:13:49,800 --> 00:13:50,800
Yes.

278
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:51,800
Don't be shy.

279
00:13:51,800 --> 00:13:52,600
Sit.

280
00:13:52,600 --> 00:13:53,400
Next to your brother.

281
00:13:53,520 --> 00:13:54,520
Okay.

282
00:13:56,400 --> 00:13:57,200
Mr. Fang.

283
00:13:57,201 --> 00:13:58,641
How did you know about our relation?

284
00:14:00,440 --> 00:14:01,880
In this business for years.

285
00:14:01,920 --> 00:14:03,720
Basic background checks are routine.

286
00:14:03,920 --> 00:14:04,440
See.

287
00:14:04,480 --> 00:14:07,279
Thought we kept it well hidden.

288
00:14:07,280 --> 00:14:08,880
Nothing to hide really.

289
00:14:09,040 --> 00:14:11,239
If I had such talented
brother as screenwriter

290
00:14:11,240 --> 00:14:12,360
I'd parade it around all the time.

291
00:14:12,400 --> 00:14:13,400
Wow.

292
00:14:13,640 --> 00:14:14,120
Make yourself at home.

293
00:14:14,200 --> 00:14:14,800
